#### `ComputePhysics`

**Input: `PhysicsRequest`**

| Field           | Type                  | Units | Shape              | Constraints              |
| --------------- | --------------------- | ----- | ------------------ | ------------------------ |
| `experiment_id` | `string`              | —     | scalar             | Non-empty, valid UUID v4 |
| `ball_configs`  | `repeated BallConfig` | —     | [B], B ∈ {1, 2, 3} | One entry per ball       |
| `mode`          | `PhysicsMode` (enum)  | —     | scalar             | See enum below           |

**`BallConfig` sub-message**

| Field                 | Type      | Units | Shape  | Constraints                            |
| --------------------- | --------- | ----- | ------ | -------------------------------------- |
| `ball_id`             | `int32`   | —     | scalar | ∈ {0, 1, 2}; must match a tracked ball |
| `mass_kg`             | `float32` | kg    | scalar | > 0.0                                  |
| `mass_uncertainty_kg` | `float32` | kg    | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                  |

```
enum PhysicsMode {
  PHYSICS_MODE_UNSPECIFIED = 0;
  SINGLE_CAMERA_PLANAR     = 1;   // 2D; uses ruler scale factor
  STEREO_3D                = 2;   // 3D; uses stereo calibration
}
```

**Output: `PhysicsResult`**

| Field    | Type                  | Units | Shape  | Constraints            |
| -------- | --------------------- | ----- | ------ | ---------------------- |
| `balls`  | `repeated BallResult` | —     | [B]    | One per ball           |
| `system` | `SystemResult`        | —     | scalar | System-level aggregate |

**`BallResult` sub-message**

| Field                         | Type      | Units  | Shape  | Constraints |
| ----------------------------- | --------- | ------ | ------ | ----------- |
| `ball_id`                     | `int32`   | —      | scalar | ∈ {0, 1, 2} |
| `v_before`                    | `float32` | m/s    | scalar | ≥ 0.0       |
| `v_before_uncertainty`        | `float32` | m/s    | scalar | ≥ 0.0       |
| `v_after`                     | `float32` | m/s    | scalar | ≥ 0.0       |
| `v_after_uncertainty`         | `float32` | m/s    | scalar | ≥ 0.0       |
| `momentum_before`             | `float32` | kg·m/s | scalar | any real    |
| `momentum_before_uncertainty` | `float32` | kg·m/s | scalar | ≥ 0.0       |
| `momentum_after`              | `float32` | kg·m/s | scalar | any real    |
| `momentum_after_uncertainty`  | `float32` | kg·m/s | scalar | ≥ 0.0       |

> **Rationale for adding `momentum_before/after_uncertainty`:** The physics engine uses the `uncertainties` library for automatic propagation through `p = mv`. Omitting the propagated uncertainty from the proto would force downstream consumers to re-derive it. The values are already computed for free inside Python; they must be transmitted.

**`SystemResult` sub-message**

| Field                                         | Type      | Units         | Shape  | Constraints                                                  |
| --------------------------------------------- | --------- | ------------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `total_momentum_before`                       | `float32` | kg·m/s        | scalar | any real                                                     |
| `total_momentum_before_uncertainty`           | `float32` | kg·m/s        | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `total_momentum_after`                        | `float32` | kg·m/s        | scalar | any real                                                     |
| `total_momentum_after_uncertainty`            | `float32` | kg·m/s        | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `ke_before`                                   | `float32` | J             | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `ke_before_uncertainty`                       | `float32` | J             | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `ke_after`                                    | `float32` | J             | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `ke_after_uncertainty`                        | `float32` | J             | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `momentum_conservation_error_pct`             | `float32` | %             | scalar | any real                                                     |
| `momentum_conservation_error_pct_uncertainty` | `float32` | %             | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |
| `coefficient_of_restitution`                  | `float32` | dimensionless | scalar | [0.0, 1.0] typically; may slightly exceed due to uncertainty |
| `coefficient_of_restitution_uncertainty`      | `float32` | dimensionless | scalar | ≥ 0.0                                                        |

> **Note:** `coefficient_of_restitution` is only meaningful for exactly 2-ball experiments. For 1- or 3-ball experiments, Python sets this to `-1.0` as a sentinel; Node checks for this before displaying.

