## 8. Edge Cases & Failure Handling

| Scenario                                     | Detection                                                                    | Recovery                                                                                                |
| -------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Python service not started yet               | `UNAVAILABLE` on first RPC call                                              | Node retries with backoff (§7); Docker `depends_on` + healthcheck should prevent this                   |
| Python service crashes mid-stream            | Stream `error` event with `UNAVAILABLE` or `INTERNAL`                        | Node surface error to UI: "Analysis service crashed. Check logs." No auto-retry for mid-stream failures |
| `experiment_id` not found on disk            | Python `os.path.exists()` fails → `NOT_FOUND`                                | UI shows "Experiment not found. Re-upload video."                                                       |
| No frames extracted (ffmpeg failed upstream) | Python lists empty directory → `INVALID_ARGUMENT`                            | UI shows "Frame extraction failed. Re-run extraction."                                                  |
| SAM2 CUDA OOM                                | `torch.cuda.OutOfMemoryError` caught → `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED`                  | UI shows "GPU memory full. Close other applications."                                                   |
| User cancels mid-tracking                    | WS `{ type: "CANCEL" }` → `stream.cancel()`                                  | Python checks `context.is_active()` per frame; returns early; partial tracks discarded                  |
| CalibrationRequest for non-existent camera   | Python finds no frames in `cam{N}/` directory                                | `NOT_FOUND` with message "No frames for camera_id=N"                                                    |
| Proto schema mismatch (stale stubs)          | Unexpected field numbers; proto3 ignores unknown fields (forward-compatible) | Unknown fields silently dropped; breaking changes require version bump (§14)                            |

### Simulation

Each failure can be simulated in tests by:

- `UNAVAILABLE`: bring Python service down before calling Node
- `NOT_FOUND`: pass a non-existent UUID as `experiment_id`
- `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED`: mock `torch.cuda.OutOfMemoryError` in `sam2_tracker.py`
- Cancellation: call `stream.cancel()` after first `data` event in Node test

