## 12. Performance Considerations

| Concern                | Analysis                                                                                                                                                         |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Message size           | `TrackingStatus` per frame: ≤ 3 balls × 2 cameras × 5 floats × 4 bytes = ~120 bytes/message. ~300 frames → ~36KB total. Negligible.                              |
| Serialisation overhead | Protobuf binary encoding: ~1µs per message. Negligible vs 200ms SAM2 frame processing.                                                                           |
| Loopback transport     | TCP loopback on Linux: ~50µs RTT. Negligible.                                                                                                                    |
| SAM2 back-pressure     | SAM2 produces one frame every ~200ms. gRPC flow control will never activate at this rate.                                                                        |
| Memory                 | Each `TrackingStatus` proto: ~120 bytes. The full stream of 300 messages: ~36KB. Retained in Node async generator queue: max 5 messages ≈ 600 bytes. Negligible. |
| CPU (proto-loader)     | `loadSync` called once at startup, not per-request. Per-call encoding/decoding: <1ms. No concern.                                                                |

**Bottleneck:** Entirely SAM2 inference speed (~200ms/frame), which is outside this module.

